lbt
------------------------------------------
This piece of software provides a C++ implementation for an algorithm that
converts a linear temporal logic formula to a generalised Büchi automaton.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.10-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.tcs.hut.fi/Software/maria/tools/lbt/

Canonical download:
  http://www.tcs.hut.fi/Software/maria/src/lbt-1.2.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack lbt-1.2.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./lbt-1.2.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/lbt-1.2.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/lbt-1.2.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(lbt)
  /usr/bin/lbt.exe
  /usr/bin/lbt2dot.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/lbt.README
  /usr/share/doc/lbt/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/lbt/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/lbt/index.html
  /usr/share/doc/lbt/notgp0-opt.png
  /usr/share/doc/lbt/notgp0.png

